2. Link : https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/find-fixed-point-value-equal-index-given-array-duplicates-allowed/
Question : Find a Fixed Point (Value equal to index) in a given array | Duplicates Allowed
Answer: Here we have to search on both left side and right side . we can not eliminate one side as elements
        may be repeated. but we can decrease the search space effectively by eleminating the values that can not be a[i]=i
        
        like   int left = magicIndex(arr, start, min(midValue,  midIndex - 1)); 
               //if (a[mid]< i) then untill a[mid] index a[i] can not be equal to i
               
               if we can not find element on left side search on right recursively.
